arch:note.arch:string: The purpose of the daily journal was to record the activities taking place in a trench each day. This included which loci were excavated, how and why loci were excavated and the ongoing impressions of the relationships among loci. It should be noted that journals record the actions, impressions and ideas of trench supervisors during the excavations. They are not, therefore, the final interpretations or syntheses of the emerging data.

arch:internalDocument.arch:string:
July 26, 2001

We will dig the SW part. We put a locus (L4021) around L4006 that is a fill. The rest of this part seems to be same so I will continue this portion's fill as that.

As we started from E heading W we immediately found an oven. Now we will take the dirt out of there then continue. A lot of pottery coming out of this locus.

We also started to take off L4009 and we found a lot of basalt pieces there. The bottom part is worn out earth again as the other surfaces that I found before. Possibly this is another outside surface.

In the SW corner of L4021 we found a sand stone piece but I am not keeping it. Also there is a little amount of bones coming out of there.

From L4021 there are too any pottery coming that I am suspicious about a possible surface. But we don't have lying pottery it seems more like a fill with many potsherds in. I opened another bag for the pottery.

I checked the section (SW) that we were finding the pottery more but I could not se anything so we are continuing with the big pick. The pottery is not coming as sitting.

Now we are taking out L4022. Stratigraphically it seems on top of L4021. Immediately we took out L4022 we hit another rock feature. There seems to be some difference in size of the stones and there were also some dirt between so I don't think these two (the new one and l4022) are same. (sloping down surface) But we don't know yet.

The other workers are cleaning and leveling L4021.

I will give another bag for the articulation of the new feature that we found because it is extending to L4021 but I don' want to mix this part. (KT 4222 and L4021)

I took out L4018. The rocks with the doorpost were even bigger than it seems. (93.38 bottom elevation of the big rock) Now we are taking the dirt below the rocks. I will give a bag to that with the same locus (4018) because it might be related. There are some more rocks below L4018 that belongs to L4025.So I will extend the dimensions of L4025to there. (There is also one of that stones with a hole there too)

The opening elevation of L4035 which is the new locus # of the oven that we found under L4021today is: 93.51

Now we are cleaning the trench.
